    "type": "message",
    "text": "REBL looks like the poor man’s version of the Smalltalk inspector to me. The Common Lisp equivalent would be Clouseau: <https://mcclim.common-lisp.dev/static/manual/mcclim.html#Inspector|https://mcclim.common-lisp.dev/static/manual/mcclim.html#Inspector>.\nAs a daily user of a next-generation Smalltalk inspector (in Glamorous Toolkit), I tend to be disappointed by these tools. Data Rabbit is a different story, it’s more a data exploration than a code development tool.",
